am\": \"April\", \"from\": 2016, \"to\": 2021}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Around 1.4 billion euros ($1.5 billion) has been spent by French authorities upgrading sewage treatment and storm water facilities around Paris to reduce the amount of untreated faecal matter flowing into the river and its main tributary, the Marne.\", \"from\": 2024, \"to\": 2273, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2082, \"end\": 2088, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.7182212736137727, \"rank\": 0.3753156926390309, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 2162, \"end\": 2167, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999979536, \"rank\": 2.0714865602290796e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Around 1.4 billion euros\", \"from\": 2024, \"to\": 2048}, {\"ngram\": \"sewage treatment\", \"from\": 2111, \"to\": 2127}, {\"ngram\": \"storm water facilities\", \"from\": 2132, \"to\": 2154}, {\"ngram\": \"the amount\", \"from\": 2178, \"to\": 2188}, {\"ngram\": \"untreated faecal matter\", \"from\": 2192, \"to\": 2215}, {\"ngram\": \"the river\", \"from\": 2229, \"to\": 2238}, {\"ngram\": \"its main tributary\", \"from\": 2243, \"to\": 2261}, {\"ngram\": \"the Marne\", \"from\": 2263, \"to\": 2272}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The cleaning-up of the Seine has been promoted as one the key legacy achievements of the Paris 2024 Games, with mayor Anne Hidalgo intending to create three public bathing areas in the river next year.\", \"from\": 2275, \"to\": 2476, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2298, \"end\": 2303, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999999986358, \"rank\": 1.1238930327443188e-12, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpe